## 📸 Mandatory E2E Evidence Rule

> ⚠️ **CRITICAL**: Every story/ticket MUST have E2E evidence captured BEFORE it can be considered complete. No exceptions.

### Requirements:
1. **Run E2E tests** if they exist for the affected flow — attach test results
2. **If no E2E test exists**, use the Playwright MCP browser to manually demonstrate the feature:
   - Navigate to the feature in the running app
   - Perform the user flow end-to-end
   - Capture a screenshot at the key moment proving the feature works
3. **Save evidence** to `evidence/S[sprint]-[story]-[description].png`
4. **Commit evidence** to the repository (on the feature branch or main)
5. **Attach evidence to the PR** as a comment (⚠️ use `--body-file` — see Shell Escaping Rule):
   ```bash
   cat > /tmp/gh-comment-body.md << 'EOF'
   ## 📸 E2E Evidence
   ![evidence](evidence/S[sprint]-[story]-[description].png)

   Feature verified via Playwright MCP browser.
   EOF
   gh pr comment [pr-number] --body-file /tmp/gh-comment-body.md
   rm -f /tmp/gh-comment-body.md
   ```
6. **Add evidence reference to the GitHub Issue** as a comment (⚠️ use `--body-file` — see Shell Escaping Rule):
   ```bash
   cat > /tmp/gh-comment-body.md << 'EOF'
   ## 📸 E2E Evidence

   Feature demonstrated and verified. Evidence captured in PR #[pr-number].

   ![evidence](https://github.ibm.com/Javier-Pacheco2/capy-pos/blob/main/evidence/S[sprint]-[story]-[description].png?raw=true)
   EOF
   gh issue comment [issue-number] --body-file /tmp/gh-comment-body.md
   rm -f /tmp/gh-comment-body.md
   ```

### Evidence Capture Steps (Playwright MCP Browser):
```bash
# 1. Start the dev server if not running
npx ng serve --port 4200 &

# 2. Use Playwright MCP browser tools:
#    - browser_navigate to http://localhost:4200
#    - Interact with the app (type, click, etc.)
#    - browser_take_screenshot to capture evidence

# 3. Copy screenshot to evidence directory
cp /private/tmp/.playwright-mcp/[screenshot].png evidence/S[sprint]-[story]-[description].png

# 4. Commit the evidence
git add evidence/
git commit -m "docs: add E2E evidence for S[sprint]-[story]"
```

### When to Capture:
- **After implementation is complete** but before PR review
- **After fixing review feedback** if the fix changes behavior
- **Before closing the issue** — evidence must exist in the repo

> 💡 This ensures every feature has verifiable proof of working correctly, creating an audit trail and preventing regressions from going unnoticed.

